Taking rogentur of ‘inviting' and reading (sor MS. aliqui) not aliquid, but in aliquid, or ab aliquo, or aliquo, he understands the allusion to be to the vexation of those who, having felt bound to invite such people as Crispus and Marcellus, found their invitation ac- cepted : praestant or praesto sunt, or se praestant.
